{#
  Light curve panel — rendered by /htmx/lightcurve.
  Expects `lc` = {"survey": str, "bands": [{"name": str, "points": [{mjd, flux, e_flux, candid}]}], "n_det": int}.
  We inline the JSON payload on a data-* attribute; lightcurve.js reads it
  and calls Chart.js. The canvas id is unique per object so htmx swaps work.
#}
<div class="tw-h-full tw-flex tw-flex-col tw-bg-bg-card tw-border tw-border-border tw-rounded tw-p-4">
  <div class="tw-flex tw-items-center tw-justify-between tw-mb-2 tw-gap-3">
    {% from "_panel_help.html.jinja" import panel_help %}
    {% call panel_help("Light curve") %}
      <div class="tw-font-semibold tw-mb-1">Navigating the chart</div>
      <ul class="tw-space-y-0.5 tw-mb-3 tw-list-disc tw-list-inside tw-text-text-secondary">
        <li>Zoom: mouse wheel (or pinch on touch)</li>
        <li>Box-zoom: <span class="mono">Shift</span> + drag</li>
        <li>Pan: <span class="mono">Ctrl</span> + drag</li>
        <li>Reset zoom: double-click the chart</li>
        <li>Select a detection: click a point (the stamps panel auto-dispatches to that detection's survey)</li>
        <li>Inspect a point: hover for survey, value, error, band, MJD</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="tw-font-semibold tw-mb-1">Two telescopes on one chart</div>
      <p class="tw-mb-2 tw-text-text-secondary">
        When this object has a counterpart on the other survey (3″ cone-search), both surveys' photometry overlays the same chart so you can compare them in one view. Marker shape encodes the telescope so it stays legible at a glance:
      </p>
      <ul class="tw-space-y-0.5 tw-mb-3 tw-list-disc tw-list-inside tw-text-text-secondary">
        <li><strong class="tw-text-text-primary">LSST</strong> — filled circles (detections), open apex-up triangles (FP)</li>
        <li><strong class="tw-text-text-primary">ZTF</strong> — filled squares (detections), open apex-down triangles (FP)</li>
        <li>Tooltip prefixes the survey label so two <em>g</em>'s can be told apart</li>
        <li>The matched cross-survey OID also shows up in the basic-info panel as a clickable link to that object's own detail view</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="tw-font-semibold tw-mb-1">Det vs FP</div>
      <ul class="tw-space-y-0.5 tw-mb-3 tw-list-disc tw-list-inside tw-text-text-secondary">
        <li><strong class="tw-text-text-primary">Det</strong> — alert-stream detections: an event triggered the alert pipeline at that epoch (positive or negative significance against the reference). The native ALeRCE data product, with stamps and a candid.</li>
        <li><strong class="tw-text-text-primary">FP</strong> — forced photometry: the survey re-extracts a flux at the object's known position whether or not an alert fired, including epochs below the alert threshold. No stamps (FP rows are clicks-no-op); useful for filling in the baseline / pre-discovery flux.</li>
        <li>ZTF FP carries the v2 <span class="mono">mag_corr</span> merge so Sci-mode error bars are reliable; LSST FP comes from a dedicated forced-photometry endpoint.</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="tw-font-semibold tw-mb-1">Legend (grouped by telescope and kind)</div>
      <ul class="tw-space-y-0.5 tw-mb-3 tw-list-disc tw-list-inside tw-text-text-secondary">
        <li>Headers like <span class="mono">LSST det:</span>, <span class="mono">LSST FP:</span>, <span class="mono">ZTF det:</span>, <span class="mono">ZTF FP:</span> separate each (telescope, kind) bucket</li>
        <li>Click a band entry to toggle just that band; click a header to toggle the whole bucket as a unit</li>
        <li>Disabled bands dim to grey instead of strikethrough; the position-residuals scatter, the periodogram input, and the CSV download all follow what's currently visible here</li>
        <li>Visibility survives every Flux/Mag, Diff/Sci, App/Abs, Obs/Der, Fold toggle</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="tw-font-semibold tw-mb-1">Axis toggles (top-right)</div>
      <ul class="tw-space-y-0.5 tw-list-disc tw-list-inside tw-text-text-secondary">
        <li><strong class="tw-text-text-primary">Diff ↔ Sci</strong> — difference vs. science flux (ZTF has science only with a reference; LSST always)</li>
        <li><strong class="tw-text-text-primary">Flux ↔ Mag</strong> — linear nJy ↔ AB magnitude (ZP 31.4, reversed axis)</li>
        <li><strong class="tw-text-text-primary">App ↔ Abs</strong> — apparent ↔ absolute (rest-frame @ 10 pc; requires z &gt; 0; Planck-2018 distance modulus)</li>
        <li><strong class="tw-text-text-primary">Obs ↔ Der</strong> — observed ↔ dereddened (Fitzpatrick 1999, A<sub>λ</sub> = R<sub>λ</sub> × E(B-V) per band; requires E(B-V) &gt; 0)</li>
        <li><strong class="tw-text-text-primary">ZTF DR</strong> — archival ZTF science photometry at this sky position (cone 1.5″); Sci mode only</li>
        <li><strong class="tw-text-text-primary">Overlay</strong> — parametric model fit from the latest feature-extractor version (SPM, FLEET, or TDE tail), when available</li>
        <li><strong class="tw-text-text-primary">Offset</strong> — visual band separation: subtract each band's mean / median / max / min, then spread by step × frequency rank (u<g<r<i<z<Y). The +/− bumps the spread by 0.1 mag; legend shows the per-band Δ in mag (multiplicative in Flux mode)</li>
      </ul>
    {% endcall %}
    <div class="tw-flex tw-items-center tw-gap-1.5 tw-flex-wrap tw-justify-end">
      {% if lc.n_det > 0 or (lc.n_fp or 0) > 0 %}
        {#
          Diff/Sci and Flux/Mag toggles are both pure client-side projections:
          points arrive with both flux values (diff + optional sci) and the JS
          picks which to plot + whether to apply the AB-ZP-31.4 mag transform.
          No server round trip.
        #}
        {#
          Cycle-buttons: one button per axis of state, showing only the
          currently active value. Click cycles to the next option; the
          button's `data-lc-*` attribute is the source of truth that the
          JS binder reads on each click.
        #}
        {% if lc.has_science_flux %}
          <button
            type="button"
            class="lc-source-toggle tw-px-1.5 tw-py-0 tw-text-[11px] tw-border tw-border-border tw-rounded tw-bg-bg-secondary tw-text-text-primary hover:tw-bg-bg-tertiary"
            data-target="lc-canvas-{{ oid }}"
            data-lc-source="diff"
            title="Click to toggle Diff ↔ Sci flux. Difference flux is from the subtracted image; science flux is the total on the science image (when a reference source exists)."
          >Diff</button>
        {% endif %}
        <button
          type="button"
          class="lc-mode-toggle tw-px-1.5 tw-py-0 tw-text-[11px] tw-border tw-border-border tw-rounded tw-bg-bg-secondary tw-text-text-primary hover:tw-bg-bg-tertiary"
          data-target="lc-canvas-{{ oid }}"
          data-lc-mode="flux"
          title="Click to toggle linear flux (nJy) ↔ AB magnitude (ZP 31.4, reversed axis)."
        >Flux</button>
        <button
          type="button"
          class="lc-abs-toggle tw-px-1.5 tw-py-0 tw-text-[11px] tw-border tw-border-border tw-rounded tw-bg-bg-secondary tw-text-text-primary hover:tw-bg-bg-tertiary"
          data-target="lc-canvas-{{ oid }}"
          data-lc-abs="app"
          title="Click to toggle Apparent ↔ Absolute (rest-frame @10 pc, via Planck-2018 distance modulus). Requires positive z."
        >App</button>
        <label
          class="tw-inline-flex tw-items-center tw-gap-1 tw-text-[11px] tw-text-text-muted"
          title="Spectroscopic redshift. Pre-filled from a TNS report when one exists for this position; otherwise empty until you click a host in the sky view or type a value in. Never inherited from the URL or a previous object."
        >
          z
          {#
            `value` is the only place a redshift gets pre-filled server-side
            — restricted to a TNS-reported z so we don't silently assume
            redshifts that haven't been confirmed for this object.
          #}
          {#
            No `value` — the deferred /htmx/tns_lookup fragment populates
            this input asynchronously when (and only when) the basic-info
            panel's TNS placeholder lands a positive redshift. Server-side
            pre-fill would block the LC render on the slow TNS bridge.
          #}
          <input
            id="lc-redshift-{{ oid }}"
            type="number"
            step="any"
            min="0"
            placeholder="z"
            data-target="lc-canvas-{{ oid }}"
            class="lc-redshift-input tw-w-[60px] tw-px-1 tw-py-0 tw-text-[11px] tw-bg-bg-secondary tw-border tw-border-border tw-rounded tw-text-text-primary tw-font-mono"
          />
        </label>
        <button
          type="button"
          class="lc-dered-toggle tw-px-1.5 tw-py-0 tw-text-[11px] tw-border tw-border-border tw-rounded tw-bg-bg-secondary tw-text-text-primary hover:tw-bg-bg-tertiary"
          data-target="lc-canvas-{{ oid }}"
          data-lc-dered="obs"
          title="Click to toggle Observed ↔ Dereddened (Fitzpatrick 1999 Milky-Way extinction, A_λ = R_λ × E(B-V) per band). Requires a positive E(B-V)."
        >Obs</button>
        <label
          class="tw-inline-flex tw-items-center tw-gap-1 tw-text-[11px] tw-text-text-muted"
          title="Milky-Way E(B-V) from the IRSA dust proxy (SF11 preferred, SFD98 fallback), cached per RA/Dec rounded to 0.01°. Leave empty for auto, or type in to override."
        >
          E(B-V)
          <input
            id="lc-ebv-{{ oid }}"
            type="number"
            step="any"
            min="0"
            placeholder="auto"
            data-target="lc-canvas-{{ oid }}"
            class="lc-ebv-input tw-w-14 tw-px-1 tw-py-0 tw-text-[11px] tw-bg-bg-secondary tw-border tw-border-border tw-rounded tw-text-text-primary tw-font-mono"
          />
        </label>
        {#
          Per-band magnitude offset for visual separation. Click "Offset" to
          reveal the centering <select> + vertical +/- micro-stepper. The
          formula is: Δ_b = −C_b + step × rank_b, where C_b is the chosen
          statistic of band b's magnitudes and rank_b follows the frequency
          ordering u<g<r<i<z<Y. Δ_b is rounded to 1 decimal mag and shown
          in the legend per band; in Flux mode it becomes a multiplicative
          10^(−Δ_b/2.5) factor with errors scaled to preserve SNR.
          Per-(survey, band) — same band on different surveys can have
          different centering values. Detection points feed the centering;
          FP and overlays inherit the same Δ_b. Periodogram and CSV stay
          on raw values.
        #}
        <button
          type="button"
          class="lc-offset-toggle tw-px-1.5 tw-py-0 tw-text-[11px] tw-border tw-border-border tw-rounded tw-bg-bg-secondary tw-text-text-muted hover:tw-bg-bg-tertiary"
          data-target="lc-canvas-{{ oid }}"
          data-lc-offset="off"
          data-lc-step="0.5"
          title="Toggle per-band magnitude offset for visual separation. When on: each band's magnitudes are subtracted by their min/median/mean/max, then spread by step × frequency rank (u<g<r<i<z<Y)."
        >Offset</button>
        <span
          class="lc-offset-wrap tw-inline-flex tw-items-center tw-gap-1 tw-hidden"
          data-target="lc-canvas-{{ oid }}"
        >
          <select
            class="lc-offset-center tw-px-1 tw-py-0 tw-text-[11px] tw-bg-bg-secondary tw-border tw-border-border tw-rounded tw-text-text-primary"
            data-target="lc-canvas-{{ oid }}"
            title="Centering statistic — each band's magnitudes are subtracted by this value before spreading."
          >
            <option value="min">min</option>
            <option value="median">median</option>
            <option value="mean">mean</option>
            <option value="max">max</option>
          </select>
          <span class="tw-inline-flex tw-flex-col tw-leading-none">
            <button
              type="button"
              class="lc-offset-step-up tw-px-1 tw-py-0 tw-text-[10px] tw-border tw-border-border tw-rounded-t tw-bg-bg-secondary tw-text-text-primary hover:tw-bg-bg-tertiary"
              data-target="lc-canvas-{{ oid }}"
              title="Increase per-rank spread by 0.1 mag (current: 0.5)."
            >^</button>
            <button
              type="button"
              class="lc-offset-step-dn tw-px-1 tw-py-0 tw-text-[10px] tw-border tw-border-t-0 tw-border-border tw-rounded-b tw-bg-bg-secondary tw-text-text-primary hover:tw-bg-bg-tertiary"
              data-target="lc-canvas-{{ oid }}"
              title="Decrease per-rank spread by 0.1 mag (current: 0.5)."
            >v</button>
          </span>
        </span>
        {#
          ZTF DR overlay — always rendered (shown for every survey when
          ra/dec are known) but hidden initially because the synchronous
          render doesn't have coords. The deferred /htmx/lc_info fragment
          calls `lcSetCoords` to stamp data-ra/data-dec and reveal it.
        #}
        <div
          id="lc-dr-wrap-{{ oid }}"
          class="lc-dr-wrap tw-inline-flex tw-items-center tw-gap-1 tw-hidden"
        >
          <button
            type="button"
            class="lc-dr-toggle tw-px-1.5 tw-py-0 tw-text-[11px] tw-border tw-border-border tw-rounded tw-bg-bg-secondary tw-text-text-muted hover:tw-text-text-primary"
            data-target="lc-canvas-{{ oid }}"
            data-lc-dr="off"
            title="Click to fetch/toggle ZTF Data Release archival photometry (cone search, 1.5 arcsec). DR points are science photometry, so they show only in Sci mode."
          >ZTF DR</button>
          {#
            Vertical alpha slider — hidden by default, revealed once DR is
            toggled on so the user can blend DR up/down dynamically without
            re-fetching. `writing-mode` + `direction: rtl` + `orient` cover
            Chromium, Firefox, and Safari vertical-range implementations;
            the inline height is explicit because flex layout can't derive
            it from a rotated child.
          #}
          <input
            type="range"
            orient="vertical"
            class="lc-dr-alpha tw-hidden"
            data-target="lc-canvas-{{ oid }}"
            min="0" max="1" step="0.01" value="0.10"
            style="writing-mode: vertical-rl; direction: rtl; width: 0.75rem; height: 2rem;"
            title="Drag to adjust ZTF DR point transparency."
          />
        </div>
        {#
          Fold button — always rendered, hidden until the deferred
          /htmx/lc_features fragment lands a positive Multiband_period and
          calls `lcSetFeatures` (which stamps data-lc-period and removes
          tw-hidden). Empty data-lc-period is the "no period yet" sentinel.
        #}
        <button
          type="button"
          class="lc-fold-toggle tw-px-1.5 tw-py-0 tw-text-[11px] tw-border tw-border-border tw-rounded tw-bg-bg-secondary tw-text-text-muted hover:tw-bg-bg-tertiary tw-hidden"
          data-target="lc-canvas-{{ oid }}"
          data-lc-fold="off"
          data-lc-period=""
          title="Click to fold the light curve at the multiband period from the feature table. Two cycles are shown side-by-side."
        >Fold</button>
        {#
          Parametric-fit overlay picker — always rendered, hidden until
          the deferred /htmx/lc_features fragment populates the per-overlay
          disabled flags. `lcSetFeatures` toggles option[disabled] based on
          which fits the object actually has (SPM / FLEET / TDE).
        #}
        <label
          id="lc-overlay-wrap-{{ oid }}"
          class="lc-overlay-wrap tw-inline-flex tw-items-center tw-gap-1 tw-text-[11px] tw-text-text-muted tw-hidden"
          title="Overlay a parametric model fit (from the latest feature-extractor version) on top of the light curve. SPM is the Sánchez-Sáez+2021 Supernova Parametric Model; FLEET and TDE-tail are the ALeRCE transient-tail models."
        >
          Overlay
          <select
            id="lc-overlay-{{ oid }}"
            class="lc-overlay-select tw-px-1 tw-py-0 tw-text-[11px] tw-bg-bg-secondary tw-border tw-border-border tw-rounded tw-text-text-primary"
            data-target="lc-canvas-{{ oid }}"
            data-lc-overlay="none"
          >
            <option value="none">none</option>
            <option value="spm" disabled>SPM</option>
            <option value="fleet" disabled>FLEET</option>
            <option value="tde" disabled>TDE tail</option>
          </select>
        </label>
        {#
          Periodogram toggle. Swaps the position-residuals panel with the
          periodogram panel (they share a grid cell). Periodogram panel
          reads MJD/flux/eflux from this LC chart and folds it back at
          the picked period — no separate folded-LC canvas. Toggle is
          aria-pressed so the highlight stays in sync.
        #}
        <button
          type="button"
          class="lc-periodogram-btn tw-px-1.5 tw-py-0 tw-text-[11px] tw-border tw-border-border tw-rounded tw-bg-bg-card tw-text-text-muted hover:tw-text-text-primary"
          data-target="lc-canvas-{{ oid }}"
          aria-pressed="false"
          onclick="window.togglePeriodogramPanel('lc-canvas-{{ oid }}')"
          title="Open the periodogram panel (replaces position residuals). Click again to switch back."
        >Periodogram</button>
        {#
          CSV export. Emits every projection as its own column — the full
          Flux/Mag × Diff/Sci × App/Abs × Obs/Der cross-product, plus the
          error alongside each. `*_abs` columns stay empty when z isn't
          set; `*_der` columns stay empty when E(B-V) isn't set, so
          consumers can tell missing-state from zero-correction. Fold is a
          display transform; rows always carry MJD, and the period lands
          in the metadata header.
        #}
        <button
          type="button"
          class="lc-download-btn tw-px-1.5 tw-py-0 tw-text-[11px] tw-border tw-border-border tw-rounded tw-bg-bg-card tw-text-text-muted hover:tw-text-text-primary"
          data-target="lc-canvas-{{ oid }}"
          data-oid="{{ oid }}"
          title="Download all 16 Flux/Mag × Diff/Sci × App/Abs × Obs/Der projections (+ errors) as CSV. Fold is display-only: rows are always MJD."
        >Download</button>
      {% endif %}
    </div>
  </div>

  {# Always rendered — `lcSetFeatures` populates it after the deferred
     features fetch lands. Hidden until then (or when overlay = "none"). #}
  <div
    id="lc-overlay-info-{{ oid }}"
    class="lc-overlay-info tw-hidden tw-font-mono tw-text-[10px] tw-text-text-secondary tw-px-1 tw-pb-1 tw-leading-snug"
    data-target="lc-canvas-{{ oid }}"
  ></div>

  {#
    Deferred-load status strip. Three independent fetches (FP, features,
    coords) fire on load and replace their own span via outerHTML; each
    fragment is now script-only and calls `lcMaybeHideLoadingStrip`, which
    collapses the strip once no `[hx-trigger~="load"]` placeholder remains
    — handing the freed vertical space back to the chart's flex-1 box. The
    canvas is already on screen by this point, so the user sees detections
    immediately and the loaders quietly disappear as each piece lands.
  #}
  {% if lc.n_det > 0 or (lc.n_fp or 0) > 0 %}
    <div
      id="lc-loading-status-{{ oid }}"
      class="tw-text-[10px] tw-text-text-muted tw-px-1 tw-pb-1 tw-flex tw-gap-3 tw-items-center tw-flex-wrap"
    >
      <span
        hx-get="{{ API_URL }}/htmx/lc_fp?oid={{ oid }}&survey_id={{ survey_id }}"
        hx-trigger="load"
        hx-swap="outerHTML"
        title="Loading forced photometry…"
      ><span class="tw-inline-block tw-animate-spin">◐</span> FP…</span>
      <span
        hx-get="{{ API_URL }}/htmx/lc_features?oid={{ oid }}&survey_id={{ survey_id }}"
        hx-trigger="load"
        hx-swap="outerHTML"
        title="Loading features (Multiband_period + parametric fits)…"
      ><span class="tw-inline-block tw-animate-spin">◐</span> features…</span>
      <span
        hx-get="{{ API_URL }}/htmx/lc_info?oid={{ oid }}&survey_id={{ survey_id }}"
        hx-trigger="load"
        hx-swap="outerHTML"
        title="Loading object coordinates (drives the dust proxy and ZTF DR overlay)…"
      ><span class="tw-inline-block tw-animate-spin">◐</span> coords…</span>
      <span
        hx-get="{{ API_URL }}/htmx/lc_xsurvey?oid={{ oid }}&survey_id={{ survey_id }}"
        hx-trigger="load"
        hx-swap="outerHTML"
        title="Looking up the matching source on the other survey (cone-search 3″)…"
      ><span class="tw-inline-block tw-animate-spin">◐</span> xsurvey…</span>
    </div>
    <div class="tw-relative tw-flex-1 tw-min-h-[15.84rem]">
      <canvas
        id="lc-canvas-{{ oid }}"
        class="lightcurve-canvas"
        data-lc='{{ lc|tojson_compact }}'
        data-ext-r='{{ extinction_r|tojson_compact }}'
      ></canvas>
    </div>
  {% else %}
    <div class="tw-text-xs tw-text-text-muted tw-py-6 tw-text-center">No detections to plot.</div>
  {% endif %}
</div>
